				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes. The PAL famiclones are designed for maximum cycle-for-cycle compatibility with Famicom software. They do this by changing the CPU to divide the master clock by 15 instead of 16, which matches the ratio of 3 dots per CPU cycle, and changing the PPU to delay NMI until line 291, which matches the duration of vertical blanking.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

